Kinetic Concepts Unit
   Sues to Block Mediq's
   Plan to Acquire ATI
Kinetic, a unit of Kinetic Concepts Inc., based here, Las
Vegas-based ATI, and Mediq's Mediq/PRN Life Support Services
Inc. unit all rent medical equipment to hospitals. Mediq is
based in Pennsauken, N.J.
   ATI and Mediq said they will oppose the suit and continue
with the proposed acquisition. ATI said the suit was without
merit.
   The $4-a-share purchase agreement has a total indicated
value of about $22 million. Completion of the transaction is
awaiting shareholder approval.
   In late trading on the American Stock Exchange yesterday,
ATI fell 12.5 cents a share to $3.125.